ked 2km, this app measured it as 1.4km. Would not recommend this app to people who is trying to actively measure the amount of calories burned through walking.', 'Used to work perfectly. Updated my OP6 to Android 10 a few days ago and since then it has stopped counting steps.', "How does a pedometer track my steps when I get up at night to put wood on the fire? The phone is on the charger on the nightstand. Also give me steps when I'm driving. Disabling, I forget to re-enable.", "Best app for monitoring your steps. Which won't connect to internet nor access your GPS. Awesome", 'More accurate than samsung health app in my galaxy.', 'Uses far too much battery power.', 'Last updated 2017', 'Would love a reset button', "With my Honor 6X I cannot find out how to keep it alive. I enabled every option I could find to prevent it from being closed but it still shuts down at some point. Also it doesn't count reliable, having the phone in my pocket does almost nothing while fiddling in my hand or typing stuff increments the counter. Already tried different sensitivities with the same results.", 'It only seems to actually save your steps count about once every billion hours or so. If you have to turn off your phone or it restarts or you run out of battery you can be out literally thousands of steps.  It would be quite good if not for this ridiculous flaw.', 'Stopped working for no reason', 'It not count steps when phone is in hand.and steps not count in ui.', 'Super. Tut genau was es soll ohne Cloud-Zwang.', 'Not counting right', 'Simple, useful. No unnecessary permissions.', 'Great but it have two issues, days not properly displays for different zones, always show UTC, and second is battery consumption. Great work.'], 'appId': 'org.secuso.privacyfriendlyactivitytracker', 'url': 'https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=org.secuso.privacyfriendlyactivitytracker&hl=en&gl=us'}
